 Fei (Chengdu, China) for their assistance. This document was edited by Sam Avrett, HIV Consultant, and Edmund Settle, HIV Policy Specialist \u2013 Human Rights and Sexual Diversity for UNDP Asia-Pacific Regional Centre. The MSM and Transgender Multi-City HIV Initiative was guided by a Steering Committee consisting of the following participants: Paul Causey, APCOM; Addy Chen, APN+; Jeremy Ross, Cristina Garces, Duanne Punpiputt, Family Health International (FHI), Asia Pacific Regional Office (APRO); Raymond Leung, Hong Kong Department of Health; Midnight Poonkasetwatana, Purple Sky Network (PSN); Geoff Manthey and James Gray, UNAIDS Regional Support Team Asia Pacific; Clifton Cortez and Edmund Settle, UNDP Asia- Pacific Regional Centre; Cameron Wolf and Panus Na Nakorn, USAID RDMA; Zhao Pengfei, World Health Organization (WHO) Western Pacific Regional Office (WPRO); Gary Reid, WHO South East Asia Regional Office (SEARO); and Peter Mok. Special thanks to FHI APRO their outstanding coordination, planning and technical support during the Initiative. Thanks are also due to the Thailand Ministry of Public Health, USAID AIDSTAR Two, the US CDC, USAID | Health Policy Initiative for the Greater Mekong Region, RTI International, Burnet Institute, amfAR Treat Asia, International HIV/AIDS Alliance, Pact, Fridae.com, UNDP and UNAIDS country offices, and the City governments for their valuable input and support throughout this effort. Edmund Settle, UNDP Asia-Pacific Regional Centre, managed the development of this report, the scan methodology, capacity support and UNDP\u2019s contribution to this Initiative. MSM and Transgender Multi-City HIV Initiative produced the following publications, which are available on the attached CD-ROM or online at http://asia-pacific.undp.org/practices/hivaids/Publications.html. 1. Towards Universal Access: Examples of Municipal HIV programming for Men who have sex with men and Transgender persons in Six Asian Cities 2. Meeting Report : Men who have sex with men and transgender populations Multi-City Initiative; City Scans and Action Planning Meeting, 7-9 December 2010 \u2013 Hong Kong 3. Methodology and Implementation Manual for Six Cities Scanning Initiative for Scale-up of HIV Responses to MSM and TG Persons 4. Reference Guide 5.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c1476693-c033-4638-a70c-4e93024b5a41": {"__data__": {"id_": "c1476693-c033-4638-a70c-4e93024b5a41", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/towards-universal-access-examples-municipal-hiv-programming-men-who-have-sex-men-and-transgender-people-six-asian-cities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Towards Universal Access: Examples of Municipal HIV Programming for Men who have Sex with Men and Transgender People in Six Asian Cities", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/towards-universal-access-examples-municipal-hiv-programming-men-who-have-sex-men-and-transgender-people-six-asian-cities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "cc0615075033988792c104e052d7b480449f7105b3947260fedaf4bc28970c12"}, "2": {"node_id": "5ab4e37d-c7d8-4e26-9bbc-35ebfe98dda1", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/towards-universal-access-examples-municipal-hiv-programming-men-who-have-sex-men-and-transgender-people-six-asian-cities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "32e33699b28f5314c3b207a