ber 2011 Date: March 2013 The views expressed in this publication are those of the participants to the Workshop on \u201cTrade, Trade Agreements and Non-Communicable Diseases\u201d held in Nadi, Fiji Islands, 11-14 February 2013, and do not necessarily represent the views of C-POND, SPC, UNDP and WHO. TRADE, TRADE AGREEMENTS AND NON-COMMUNICABLE DISEASES IN THE PACIFIC ISLANDS ii iii This report summarises the proceedings of the Sub-Regional Workshop on \u201cTrade, Trade Agreements and Non-Communicable Diseases\u201d held in Nadi, Fiji Islands, 11-14 February 2013. The event was sponsored by SPC, UNDP Pacific Centre and WHO. The report was jointly prepared by the four agencies and produced by UNDP Pacific Centre. Organizing Team Pacific Research Centre for the Prevention of Obesity and Non-communicable Diseases (C-POND): Dr Wendy Snowdon Secretariat of the Pacific Community (SPC): Jeanie McKenzie, Dr Viliami Puloka United Nations Development Programme (UNDP): Adelle Khan, Ahmed Moustafa, Samita Singh, Ferdinand Strobel, Simone Troller World Health Organization (WHO): Dr Colin Bell, Peter Hoejskov, Amele Maravou, Dr Temo Waqanivalu Faculty Team Dr Deborah Gleeson (La Trobe University) Dr David Legge (La Trobe University) Dr Benn McGrady (Georgetown University) Dr Wendy Snowdon (C-POND, Deakin University and Fiji National University) Dr Anne Marie Thow (University of Sydney) Additional Resource Persons, Panellists and Observers Mr Nicky Anaturin (PIFS) Mr. David Clarke (Allen & Clarke \u2013New Zealand) Prof. Carlos Correa (University of Buenos Aires/ UNDP) Ms Margaret Eastgate (Oceania National Olympic Committees) Ms Mere Falemaka (Melanesian Spear Group Secretariat) Ms Eva Jarawan (The World Bank) Mr Brian Lutz (UNDP) Ms Elenoa Puamau (Fiji National University) Mr Ronseh Prasad (Fiji National University) Ms Paulini Sesevu (AusAID) Dr. Sripen Tantivess (Ministry of Health Thailand) Mr. Kazuyuki Uji (UNDP APRC) Dr. Godfrey Xuereb (WHO) Ms. Joann Young (PIFS) Country 